{
  "texts": [
    "Feature definition depends on the data source.",
    "For compound-target associations predicted by our deep learning model, r(c, g) is the normalized consensus rank of gene g in the compound's putative target list, and feature x is defined as the odd ratio:",
    "For the compound activity profile matrix, q was the Pearson correlation coefficient of the pharmacological profiles between a query compound c and a reference compound c 0.",
    "Considering multiple reference compounds {c 0 i } may exist for a target g, the maximum value of q was used as the feature:",
    "When NCI 60 or PSP activity profiles were used for modeling, q refers to the Pearson correlations in the corresponding activity matrices."
  ]
}